HEADWORD: Duramen
<hw>Du*ra"men</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., hardness, a
hardened, <it>i. e.</it>, ligneous, vine branch, fr. <ets>durare</ets>
to harden. See <er>Dure</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
heartwood of an exogenous tree.</def>⟦br⟧
